1. How to create a class, object, method and its signature.
Solution:
Class: To create a class use "class" Keyword.
Example: 
public class Main {
  int M = 50;
}

Object: In Java, an object is created from a class.
Example:
public class Main{
int M = 50;
public static void main(String[] args) {
Main myObj=new Main();
System.Out.Println(myObj.x);
}
}
Method:It is a block of code or collection of statements
Example:
public class Main   
{  
public static void main(String[] args)   
{    
System.out.print("The max num is: " + Math.max(9,7));  
}  
}  

2. Write a program to print your name.
import java.util.Scanner;
public class Main {
  public static void main(String[] args) 
  {
    Scanner sc = new Scanner (System.in);
    System.out.print("Input your First name: ");
    String fname = sc.next();
    System.out.print("Input your Last name: ");
    String lname = sc.next();
    System.out.print(fname+" "+lname);
  }
}

3.Write a program for a Single line comment, multi-line and documentation comments.

Single line comment:Used to comment only one line of the code.
Syntax://
public class Main {    
public static void main(String[] args) {    
int i=10; // i is a variable with value 10  
System.out.println(i);  //printing the variable i  
}    
}    

Mutli line comment: /* and */

public class Main {    
public static void main(String[] args) {    
/* Let's declare and  
 print variable in java. */    
  int i=10;    
    System.out.println(i);    
/* float j = 9.9; 
    float k = 4.9; 
    System.out.println( j + k ); */    
}    
}    

Define variables for different Data Types int, Boolean, char, float, double and print on the 
 Console.
 solution:
 
 class Test {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int a=10;
        double b = 123.43555;
        char c = 'e';
        boolean d = true;
        float e=3.1f;
        System.out.println("int: " + a);
        System.out.println("Double: " + b);
        System.out.println("Character: " + c);
        System.out.println("Boolean: " + d);
        System.out.println("float: " + e);
    }
}

Define the local and Global variables with the same name and print both variables and 
understand the scope of the variables.
Local Variable:

public int add(){
int a =4;
int b=5;
return a+b;

Global Variable:
int a =4;
int b=5;
public int add(){
return a+b;
}
}


6. Write a function to print your name and call the function from main method.
public class Main {
  static void myMethod() {
    System.out.println("Hi, This is Naveen!!1");
  }

  public static void main(String[] args) {
    myMethod();
  }
}
